content.description:
Great climb with a good variety of finger crack, and face climbing. The faces are highly textured and the two horizontal flaws are a fun challenge to solve.

Start with right facing finger crack. Stem to mantle into first horizontal flaw. Crux, for me, was between booth flaws, on this face there was a "bubble wrap" type texture with some hard to grip edges. Mantle into second flaw and then hang off jugs to the top.
content.protection: Bolted route. Nine bolts with two bolt anchor (no rap rings). Anchor is setback from edge about two feet.
content.location: Left most route, of two, on climbers left. Rappel in to start. Starts on top of large boulder.

content.description: Face climb up well textured rock. 5.10A rating comes from one single move.
content.protection: Bolted route. Eight bolts and two bolt anchor without rap rings. Anchor is set back from the top about two feet.
content.location: Route on climbers right. Rappel in to start
